<header>
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1 tabindex="1">Exercise 3 - Notifications and Focus Management</h1>
    <div>
      {{link-to 'View all exercises' 'index'}}
    </div>
  </div>
</header>
<div class="a11y-exercise">
  <contentinfo role="contentinfo">
    <h2 id="ally-learning-objectives">Learning Objectives</h2>
    <div class="a11y-exercise-learning-objectives">
      <ol aria-labelledby="ally-learning-objectives">
        <li>Participants should be able to use ember conventions to draw attention (focus) to a component.</li>
        <li>Participants should be able to use roles and aria attributes to make a "modal component" more accessible
          to keyboard and screen reader users.
        </li>
        <li>Participants should understand when it is appropriate to use tabindex, and which values are appropriate to
          use with tabindex.
        </li>
        <li>Participants should be able to describe the heading-order and tabindex AXE rules.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    <h2 id="a11y-instructions">Instructions</h2>
    <div class="a11y-exercise-instructions">
      <ol aria-labelledby="a11y-instructions">
        <li>Update the <code>a11y-workshop-modal.js</code> component to focus the modal content after it renders.</li>
        <li>Add an a11y audit to the <code>focus-management-test.js</code> test.</li>
        <li>Fix all accessibility violations.</li>
        <li>Use aria attributes in the <code>a11y-workshop-modal.js</code> component to be labelled by the title in the
          modal.
        </li>
        <li>Use aria attributes in the <code>a11y-workshop-modal.js</code> component to be described by hidden text that describes the modal.</li>
        <li>Add a role of 'dialog' to the <code>a11y-workshop-modal.js</code> component.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </contentinfo>
  <main>
    <h2>Results</h2>
    <div class="a11y-exercise-results">
      <div class="exercise-3-controls">
        <button onclick={{action (mut showModal) (not showModal)}}>Show Modal</button>
        <div>
          {{link-to 'Back to all exercises' 'index'}}
        </div>
        <div>
          <button>This button doesn't do anything</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</div>

{{#if showModal}}
  {{#a11y-workshop-modal}}
    <h4 class="focus-management-modal-heading">This is a modal that requires an action!</h4>
    <label>Make a choice.</label>
    <select class="focus-management-modal-select">
      <option>1</option>
      <option>2</option>
      <option>3</option>
    </select>
    <div class="focus-management-modal-options">
      <button onclick={{action (mut showModal) false}}>Dismiss the modal</button>
      <button onclick={{action (mut somethingExciting) true}}>Do something</button>
    </div>
  {{/a11y-workshop-modal}}
{{/if}}